Here are both approaches:

**1. Register the route** in `AppShell.xaml.cs`:

```csharp
Routing.RegisterRoute("productdetails", typeof(ProductDetailsPage));
```

**2. Navigate from ProductListPage** (ViewModel or code-behind):

```csharp
// â”€â”€ Approach A: string query parameter â”€â”€
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"productdetails?productId={product.Id}");

// â”€â”€ Approach B: pass the full object â”€â”€
var parameters = new ShellNavigationQueryParameters
{
    { "product", product }
};
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("productdetails", parameters);
```

**3. Receive on the target ViewModel** with `IQueryAttributable`:

```csharp
public class ProductDetailsViewModel : ObservableObject, IQueryAttributable
{
    private string _productId;
    private Product _product;

    public string ProductId
    {
        get => _productId;
        set => SetProperty(ref _productId, value);
    }

    public Product Product
    {
        get => _product;
        set => SetProperty(ref _product, value);
    }

    public void ApplyQueryAttributes(IDictionary<string, object> query)
    {
        // Approach A â€“ string parameter arrives as object, call ToString()
        if (query.TryGetValue("productId", out var id))
        {
            ProductId = id.ToString();
            // Load full product from a service using the ID...
        }

        // Approach B â€“ full object via ShellNavigationQueryParameters
        if (query.TryGetValue("product", out var obj) && obj is Product p)
        {
            Product = p;
            ProductId = p.Id;
        }
    }
}
```

**4. Wire the ViewModel** as `BindingContext` on `ProductDetailsPage`:

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             xmlns:vm="clr-namespace:MyApp.ViewModels"
             x:Class="MyApp.Views.ProductDetailsPage"
             x:DataType="vm:ProductDetailsViewModel">
    <!-- Shell calls ApplyQueryAttributes on the BindingContext automatically -->
</ContentPage>
```

**Key points:**

| | Query string (`?key=val`) | `ShellNavigationQueryParameters` |
|---|---|---|
| **Data types** | Strings only | Any object |
| **Serialization** | URL-encoded | None (passed by reference) |
| **Back-nav friendly** | Yes (URI is reconstructable) | Object may be lost on back-nav |
| **Use when** | Simple IDs, flags | Complex/large objects already in memory |

> **Tip:** Always `await` `GoToAsync` â€” fire-and-forget causes silent race conditions. And if your ViewModel is registered via DI, Shell will auto-resolve it as the `BindingContext`, triggering `ApplyQueryAttributes` for you.
